Suggested core use cases for PopuList 3.0 dataset:
1. Track the rise/spread of populism over time (using populist_start, populist_end across countries and periods);
2. Analyze populism’s relationship to government power (filter on in_parliament, compare populist parties holding office and their policy behavior, e.g., on COVID);
3. Compare populist ideologies and associated policy stances (far-right/left/centrist, Euroscepticism, climate, pandemic response);
4. Merge with other datasets (OxCGRT, electoral, economic, survey data, using country_name, party_name_short, parlgov_id, partyfacts_id);
Includes suggested visuals (timelines, maps, stacked area charts, scatter plots), technical usage notes, and examples of research questions.
